{"id":19224,"title":"Staphylococcus aureus bacteremia without a localizing source in pediatric patients.","abstract":"Staphylococcus aureus bacteremia without a localizing source in children is not well described. We identified patients with a positive blood culture for S. aureus from an 11-year surveillance study. Thirty-six cases of primary bacteremia were identified accounting for 5.7% of bacteremias. Most patients had comorbidities (86.1%), most commonly immunosuppression (33.3%). ","date":"2014-04-15","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24732394","annotations":[{"name":"Culture","weight":0.482132,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Culture"},{"name":"Blood culture","weight":0.355556,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood_culture"},{"name":"Immunosuppression","weight":0.213889,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Immunosuppression"},{"name":"Staphylococcus aureus","weight":0.163889,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Staphylococcus_aureus"},{"name":"Blood","weight":0.130838,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood"},{"name":"Pediatrics","weight":0.129065,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pediatrics"},{"name":"Bacteremia","weight":0.0711346,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bacteremia"},{"name":"Staphylococcus","weight":0.0546925,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Staphylococcus"},{"name":"Aureus","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aureus"},{"name":"Accountancy","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Accountancy"},{"name":"Surveillance","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surveillance"},{"name":"Comorbidity","weight":0.0119316,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comorbidity"}]}
